{% extends 'base.html.twig' %}

{% block title %}Timestamp Microservice{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
    <h1 class="header">
        Timestamp microservice
    </h1>
    User stories:
    <ol>
        <li>You can pass a string as a parameter, and it will check to see whether that string contains either a unix timestamp or a natural language date (example: January 1, 2016)</li>
        <li> If it does, it returns both the Unix timestamp and the natural language form of that date.</li>
        <li> If it does not contain a date or Unix timestamp, it returns null for those properties.</li>
    </ol>

    </section>
    <section id="usage">
        <h2>Example usage:</h3>
            <p>If you want to use natural data string as parameter:</p>
            <div>
                <code>{{ path('timestamp.api', {timestr: normal}) }}</code>
            </div>
            <p>If you want to use <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Unix_time">unix timestamp</a> as parameter</p>
            <div>
                <code>{{ path('timestamp.api', {timestr: unix}) }}</code>
            </div>
    </section>
    <section id="output">
        <h2>Example output:</h3>
            <code>
				<pre>
{
    "unix": 1497474000,
    "natural": "June 15, 2017"
}				</pre>
            </code>
{% endblock %}